== Course Outline

#dblock(title: [Fundamentals of AI applied to the Web])[
  Some initial concepts to the area, describing the basic taxonomy of Web Mining and some practical uses of its components and recap of Data Mining and Machine Learning topics.
]

#dblock(title: [Web Content Mining])[
  We will define the main web contents that we can find (mainly text), how we can retrieve them and how we can use it to describe and compare between web pages in a theoretical and practical way.
]

== Course Outline

#dblock(title: [Web Structure Mining])[
  We will describe how we can characterize the structure of the web, what is the value behind it and some tools to achieve it. Of course, we will review some practical uses and applications that are part of the state of the art in this topic.
]

#dblock(title: [Web Usage Mining])[
  We will characteize the use of the web from two points of view. One from the _records_ generated by its use and another from the _content_ generated by its use. It will be described what we can do with these characterizations, practical uses and some tool to apply it.
]


== Course Outline

#dblock(title: [Intelligent Agents on the Web])[
  We will learn the fundamentals of intelligent agents and their application on the Web. We will explore agent architectures based on large language models (LLMs) and use frameworks and apply these tool to solve real-world problems.
]

#dblock(title: [Human-Computer Interaction and Intelligent Interfaces])[
  We will focus on the design and evaluation of adaptive and conversational interfaces for web-based problems.
]

